  "lemmas": {
    "OPEN": {
      "name": "OPEN_high_tag_and_deployed_Mpad",
      "statement": "(1) Inject residual free-1 highs into [K] with K\u22642176 (=\u230ae/\u230an/e\u230b\u230b), or prove residual A_SP pairs use \u22642176 highs with an explicit \u03ba.\n(2) M_pad\u22641 (or \u22642 via core packing) at free_core=846161: need multipad-core disjointness or other free_core\u226b1 control; toys show core intersections when free_core\u22652.",
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    "UV_disjoint": {
      "name": "free1_CS_sides_disjoint",
      "proof": [
        "v25 free-1 high family packing."
      ],
      "statement": "Any free-1 CS ordered pair (U,V) has U \u2229 V = \u2205. Proof: same free-1 high H \u21d2 both in F_H \u21d2 pairwise disjoint (v25).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "fc1_Mpad": {
      "deployed_floor_n_minus_2e_over_mc": 2,
      "deployed_floor_n_over_mc": 2,
      "deployed_note": "Deployed free_core=846161 \u2260 1, so this bound does not apply. Numerically \u230a(n\u22122e)/m_c\u230b = 2 and \u230an/m_c\u230b = 2 \u2014 packing would give M_pad\u22642 if multipad cores were disjoint at free_core\u226b1 (OPEN).",
      "name": "free_core_1_M_pad_packing_bound",
      "proof": [
        "v23: free_core=1 multipad cores are free-1 CS of degree m_c.",
        "v25 applied to m_c-sets with free-1 high (= depth-(m_c\u22121) multi-mates): free-1 family pairwise disjoint.",
        "Joint avoidance: cores \u2286 D \\ (U \u222a V).",
        "U \u2229 V = \u2205 \u21d2 |U \u222a V| = 2e.",
        "Disjoint m_c-sets in a ground set of size n\u22122e \u21d2 bound."
      ],
      "statement": "Suppose free_core = 1 (so m_c = w+1). For any multipad side pair (U,V), the multipad cores form a free-1 CS clique of m_c-sets (v23) with a common free-1 high H_core, hence are pairwise disjoint and lie in D \\ (U \u222a V). Therefore M_pad \u2264 \u230a(n \u2212 |U \u222a V|) / m_c\u230b = \u230a(n \u2212 2e) / m_c\u230b (using |U \u222a V| = 2e from side disjointness).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "high_tag": {
      "deployed": {
        "K_max": 2176,
        "K_max_times_floor": 67456,
        "e": 67472,
        "fits": true,
        "floor_n_over_e": 31
      },
      "name": "residual_high_tag_payment_criterion",
      "proof": [
        "v20: M_pad\u22641 \u21d2 pairs inject via side geometry; N_ord = N_side.",
        "v25: within F_H, (\u03b9,\u03b4) injective and |F_H|\u2264\u230an/e\u230b.",
        "\u03ba injective on residual highs \u21d2 (\u03ba(H),\u03b9(U),\u03b4) injective globally on residual pairs (pairs are always mono-high).",
        "Cardinality: |\u03ba|\u00b7|\u03b9|\u00b7|\u03b4| \u2264 K\u00b7\u230an/e\u230b\u00b7p \u2264 e\u00b7p."
      ],
      "statement": "Assume M_pad \u2264 1. Suppose residual free-1 highs (those appearing among residual top-seam free-1 CS pairs) inject into a label set of size K with K \u00b7 \u230an/e\u230b \u2264 e. Let \u03b9: F_H \u2192 {0,..,|F_H|\u22121} \u2286 [\u230an/e\u230b] be the within-family rank (v25). Then (U,V) \u21a6 (\u03ba(H), \u03b9(U), \u03b4) with \u03b4 = c0U\u2212c0V injects residual free-1 CS ordered pairs into a set of size \u2264 K\u00b7\u230an/e\u230b\u00b7p \u2264 e\u00b7p = t\u00b7p = 143763024447376, hence |A_SP| \u2264 t\u00b7p.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "single_high": {
      "name": "single_residual_high_closes_payment",
      "proof": [
        "High-tag criterion with K=1; v25 within-family marks."
      ],
      "statement": "If M_pad\u22641 and residual free-1 CS pairs use only one high (K=1 \u2264 K_max), then (\u03b9,\u03b4) alone injects into e\u00b7p and |A_SP|\u2264t\u00b7p.",
      "status": "PROVED",
      "toy_note": "Multi-high fibers occur on toys \u2014 single-high is not automatic."
    }
  },
